HEADWORD: Synalepha
<hw>Syn`a*le"pha</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>synaloepha</ets>, Gr. <?/, from <?/ to melt together;
<grk>sy`n</grk> with + <?/ to besmear.]</ety> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A
contraction of syllables by suppressing some vowel or diphthong at the
end of a word, before another vowel or diphthong; <as>as, <ex>th'
army</ex>, for <ex>the army</ex></as>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>synaloepha</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

